ce:section.ce:para:
The N,S−CQDs were produced from the tartaric acid and taurine precursors, as mentioned above (Scheme 1
                        ). The TEM observation confirmed the formation of nearly spherical N,S−CQDs along with the diameter ranges from 2 to 3 nm (Fig. 1
                        a). As presented in Fig. 1b, the broad XRD peak at 25° along with (002) reflection confirmed the amorphous nature of N,S−CQDs.[33] This outcome is consistent with the result attained from the broad ring in selected area electron diffraction SAED micrograph (Fig. 1c). The FTIR spectrum of N,S−CQDs (Fig. 1d) reveals the peak at 590 cm-1, 1105 cm-1, 1250 cm-1, 2860 cm-1, 2919 cm-1, and 3421 cm-1 advocated the occurrence of C−S, C−O, C−N, −C−H, =C−H, and –OH/−NH stretching or bending vibrations. The characteristic peaks at 1641 cm-1, and 1445 cm-1 are due to the HN−C=O and aromatic ring C=C−C, respectively; this result established that as-prepared nanomaterial possesses some graphene like structure [34].
